@startuml
!include <C4/C4_Context>
!include <C4/C4_Container>
!include <C4/C4_Component>

allowmixing

/'
C4 – Code Diagram

Purpose:
Provides a focused view of selected implementation details inside a single *Component,
when this level of detail is necessary to explain complex or non-obvious design decisions.

Scope:
- Exactly one *Component from the C3 Component Diagram
- Only *Code Elements that are essential to understanding behavior, responsibilities,
  or extension points should be shown

*Component:
- The component being explored at code level

*Code Elements:
- Classes, interfaces, or key data structures within the component
- Only include elements that contribute to understanding design, responsibilities, or extension points

*Relationships:
- Relationships between code elements (e.g., usage, inheritance,
  implementation, composition)
- Direction of dependencies should be explicit where it matters

Design Notes:
- This level is optional and should be used sparingly
- Common or trivial code structures should be omitted
- Design patterns may be illustrated when they are central to the design
  (e.g., Factory, Strategy, Observer, Adapter)
- This diagram is not a complete UML class diagram
- The goal is explanation, not exhaustiveness
'/

Container_Boundary(recipe_repo_boundary, "Recipe Repository") {
    class RecipeRepository {
        +GetById(id: string): Recipe
        +Save(recipe: Recipe)
    }

    class Recipe {
        +Id: string
        +Title: string
        +Instructions: string
    }
}

ContainerDb(database, "Database", "Relational Database", "Stores recipe text and metadata.")

RecipeRepository ..> Recipe : uses
RecipeRepository --> database : reads from and writes to

@enduml

